// [v2.10.0 SHELL-1] CyberTheme DELETED. It was a second, complete, hardcoded palette
// (#00ff88 acid green, #ff00ff magenta, #00d4ff cyan, #0a0a0f) living alongside the --ae-*
// token system and shadowing it. Seven live call sites read from it, including
// getCyberIconHTML('settings', CyberTheme.colors.accentSecondary) in the Theme Forge's own
// header — hardcoded magenta, in the theme editor, immune to every theme it can author.
// No theme could ever reach any of it. Every one of those sites now passes no colour at
// all, so the icon renderers fall to their own currentColor default and take the colour
// from CSS on the parent, which is where a theme can actually reach it.
// Deleted rather than left unread: a hardcoded palette sitting in the file is an invitation
// to reach for it again, and the next person to do so would be re-creating the exact bug.

